      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOLDEN SUNSET (8) has been knocking on the door for a while and went close again last time, finishing third and just 2.6 metres from the winner. Can travel in a nice spot from this draw and wait on the sprint lane if necessary. The longer distance may suit her. Leading hope. MUFASA METRO NZ (5) did a good job to beat GOLDEN SUNSET for a resuming win at this venue a fortnight ago. Draws wider but hasn't missed a place in seven second-up attempts so could go on with it. Manners have let ALDEBARANSTILINSKI (2) down in two starts since he put a string of wins together. Placed in a trial since the last-start fourth. Draws well and can win if he gets it right. HIDE AND SEEK (7) must be considered after he finished third here two weeks ago.",
